layers.nm: This function uses the Gaussian elimination method to solve a system of linear equations. - It takes two parametersS: coeficients (a matrix of coefficients) and vector (a vector of constants). It first checks if the input is valid (i.e. if the coefficients matrix is square and the vector is a single column). If the input is valid, it creates an augmented matrix by combining the coefficients and vector. It then scales the matrix, leaving it triangular. Finally, it uses the retroactive resolution method to solve the system of linear equations and returns the solution as an array.
